      "slack emoji constraints",
      "animation primitives",
      "gif optimization",
      "slack message graphics"
    ],
    "actual_capabilities": [
      "Create animated GIFs with 13 animation primitives (shake, bounce, spin, pulse, fade, zoom, explode, wiggle, slide, flip, morph, move, kaleidoscope)",
      "Validate GIF files against Slack size limits (64KB for emoji, 2MB for messages)",
      "Optimize GIFs with color quantization and frame reduction",
      "Build GIFs programmatically from frames using the GIFBuilder class",
      "Apply easing functions for natural motion (ease_in, ease_out, bounce, elastic)"
    ],
    "limitations": [
      "Requires pillow, imageio, and numpy Python libraries",
      "No built-in image import from files (frames must be generated programmatically)",
      "Emoji GIFs have strict 64KB limit requiring aggressive optimization",
      "Text rendering is basic and optimized for small sizes only"
    ],
    "use_cases": [
